  "body": "Hello, I received a weird case. I'm sending the wrong transaction (I know about it, but want to see it on etherscan).\r\n\r\nThis code returned an error before sending:\r\n\r\n```\r\nawait dt.callSomeMethod(1)\r\nUncaught ProviderError: The execution failed due to an exception.\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor this transaction, the code is working (and I can look on the transaction):\r\n```\r\nawait contract.callSomeMethod(1, {gasLimit: 30000000})\r\n{\r\n  hash: '...',\r\n  type: 2,\r\n  accessList: []\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nHow can I force send a transaction (if I know about it)? Or is it a problem on the node side?",
